'''Doorstep''' is a Norwegian company.
It was established in 2000, and was meant to develop a [[web portal]] for [[online trade]]. It was a cooperation between telecommunications company [[Telenor]] and [[Den norske Bank]]. Chairman was Petter Jansen, and among the board members were [[Gunn Wærsted]], [[Jon Fredrik Baksaas]] and [[Ingvild Myhre]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Hånd i hånd om e-handel|last=Egede-Nissen|first=Heidi|date=31 October 2000|work=Dagens Næringsliv|page=11|language=Norwegian}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Åpner for banktopper|last=Egede-Nissen|first=Heidi|date=18 January 2001|work=Dagens Næringsliv|page=7|language=Norwegian}}</ref> The goal was to create the largest market place of its kind in Norway. However the chief executive officer Knut Oppegaard quit in March 2001 and was replaced by Ann-Kristin Hageløkken. The portal had not yet been opened.<ref>{{cite news|title=Reduserte ambisjoner|last=|first=|date=8 March 2001|work=Dagens Næringsliv|page=28|language=Norwegian}}</ref> The plans were then significantly altered in April 2001, as the plans for online trading were cut. It shared its fate with several [[dot-com company|dot-com companies]],<ref>{{cite news|title=DnB/Telenor-nettbutikk skrinlagt|last=|first=|date=3 April 2001|work=Aftenposten|page=44|language=Norwegian}}</ref> although the company would use the [[.no]] [[top-level domain]] instead of [[.com]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Vital på nett med skadeforsikring|last=|first=|date=8 December 2000|work=Bergens Tidende|page=17|language=Norwegian}}</ref>
The company still exists, with the purpose of "business development". Jon Fredrik Baksaas is a member of the board, which is now chaired by [[Rune Bjerke]].<ref>[http://www.doorstep.no/Velkommen.html Official site] {{no icon}}</ref>
