'''Jurgens Ci Caravans''' Ltd, founded in 1952, is South Africa’s oldest and largest [[Caravan (towed trailer)|caravan]] manufacturer. The company operates from a head office in [[Ga-Rankuwa]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://caravansa.co.za/articles/2012-past-issues/august-magazine-preview/the-jurgens-story-famous-caravan-manufacturers-in-south-africa |title=The Jurgens story. Famous Caravan Manufacturers in South Africa |publisher=Caravansa.co.za |accessdate=18 November 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129025721/http://caravansa.co.za/articles/2012-past-issues/august-magazine-preview/the-jurgens-story-famous-caravan-manufacturers-in-south-africa |archivedate=29 November 2014 |df= }}</ref> north of [[Pretoria]], [[Gauteng]], and has a canvas division<ref>Stammer, Gunther; Laing, Keith (2014). ''60 Years of Caravanning in South Africa''. South Africa: Jurgens Ci (Pty) Ltd. p. 97. {{ISBN|978-0-620-59065-5}}.</ref> in New Germany, KwaZulu-Natal. The company was founded in [[Germiston]] in 1952 by Geert Jurgens and his sons, Dirk and Rieks, who emigrated to South Africa from the [[Netherlands]] in 1950.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jurgensci.co.za/2 |title=Jurgens Ci - Caravan Manufacturers, South Africa, Jurgens, Gypsey, Sprite, WJ Motorhomes, Jurgens Safari,Howling Moon, CAMPWORLD |publisher=Jurgensci.co.za |accessdate=18 November 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140921134050/http://www.jurgensci.co.za/2 |archivedate=21 September 2014 |df= }}</ref>
Over a history spanning 60 years,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://doitnow.co.za/content/jurgens-still-going-strong-after-60-years|title=Jurgens Still Going Strong After 60 Years|publisher=Doitnow.co.za|accessdate=18 November 2014}}</ref> the company has helped to drive South Africa’s domestic tourism market and has responded to changing market needs by adding add pop-tops, off-road caravans, motorhomes, truck bodies, luggage trailers, canvas products and off-road trailers to its product range.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/profiles/companies/845059Z:SJ-jurgens-ci-pty-ltd|title=Jurgens Ci Pty Ltd: Company Profile - Bloomberg|work=Bloomberg|accessdate=18 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://caravansa.co.za/articles/2012-past-issues/july-magazine-preview/jurgens-caravan-manufacturer-south-africa-part-2 |title=The Jurgens Caravan Story: Part 2 |publisher=Caravansa.co.za |accessdate=18 November 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129025820/http://caravansa.co.za/articles/2012-past-issues/july-magazine-preview/jurgens-caravan-manufacturer-south-africa-part-2 |archivedate=29 November 2014 |df= }}</ref>
The company is a wholly owned subsidiary of [[Imperial Holdings]] Ltd. Jurgens provides employment for 970 in South Africa and has 70 employees in [[Australia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.financialresults.co.za/2011/imperial_2011/ar2011/divisional-review-automotive-retail.php|title=Imperial Annual Report 2011 - Divisional review- Automotive retail|publisher=Financialresults.co.za|accessdate=18 November 2014}}</ref>
Jurgens Ci has a dealer network in South Africa and [[Namibia]], and exports units to Australia, the Netherlands and [[New Zealand]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://jurgens.com.au/About-Us.aspx|title=Jurgens Australia - About Us|publisher=Jurgens.com.au|accessdate=18 November 2014}}</ref> Jurgens also has a production facility in [[Melbourne]], Australia.
