{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}} {{Use British English|date=April 2018}} '''Kjeld Anker Ammentorp''' (10 November 1895 – 23 October 1975) was the founder of [[RMC Group]], one of the [[United Kingdom]]'s largest [[concrete]] businesses.
==Career== Born in [[Frederiksberg]] in [[Denmark]], Kjeld Ammentorp moved to the [[United Kingdom]] in 1919.<ref name=kjeld>[http://www.ammentorp.org/genealogy/ps01/ps01_050.htm Ammentorp Genealogy]</ref> A [[civil engineer]] by training, Ammentorp took advantage of the invention of self-agitating cement trucks in the 1920s.<ref name=kjeld/> He built his first plant in 1930 at [[Bedfont]] in [[London]], bought cement mixers from [[Denmark]] and expanded his business into one of the largest in the [[United Kingdom]].<ref>[https://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/2895898/Ready-mixed-fortunes.html Ready Mixed Fortunes] Daily Telegraph, 28 September 2004</ref>
In 1952 he sold his company to Sam Stirling who had developed a similar business in [[Australia]].<ref name=kjeld/> Ammentorp remained on the Board of the Company until 1958 but retired to [[Denmark]] in 1961.<ref name=kjeld/>
He died in 1975 at [[Gentofte]] and is buried in [[Frederiksberg]].<ref>[http://freepages.genealogy.rootsweb.ancestry.com/~eschricht/esch/d0004/g0000004.html#I6904 Kjeld Ammentorp at Ancestry.com]</ref>
==Family==
In May 1920 he married Tordis Giersing at St. James's Church in [[London]].
